Well Depth Monitoring

require(formhub, quietly = T)
require(ggplot2, quietly = T)
wells <- formhubRead("~/Downloads/well_Inventory_ver_0_4_2014_01_17_14_53_10.csv", 
    "~/Downloads/well_Inventory_ver_0_4.json", keepGroupNames = F)
depths <- formhubRead("~/Downloads/ob_well_data_1_2014_01_17_14_52_14.csv", 
    "~/Downloads/ob_well_data_1.json", keepGroupNames = F)
depths_with_well_info <- merge(wells, depths, by = "Well_ID")
depths_with_well_info$ReducedWaterLevel <- with(depths_with_well_info, location_source._geopoint_source_altitude - 
    waterlevel.swl)

ggplot(depths_with_well_info, aes(x = date_recording, y = ReducedWaterLevel, 
    color = Well_ID)) + geom_line() + labs(x = "Date of recording", y = "Water level in meters", 
    color = "Well ID", title = "Water levels over time")


# ggsave('WaterLevelsOverTime.png')

ggplot(depths_with_well_info, aes(x = resource.measurements_wd, y = ReducedWaterLevel, 
    color = Well_ID)) + geom_jitter() + labs(x = "Well depth in meters", y = "Water level in meters", 
    color = "Well ID", title = "Water level vs. well depth")

Contour plots by Month

Note: the following graphs use Spline Interpolation, particularly the Akima Spline

require(akima, quietly = T)
require(lubridate, quietly = T)
require(RColorBrewer, quietly = T)
depths_with_well_info$month <- round_date(depths_with_well_info$date_recording, 
    "month")
d_ply(depths_with_well_info, .(month), function(df) {
    if (nrow(df) > 4) {
        # akima interpolation requires 4 points minimum
        print(unique(df$month))
        xyz <- with(df, data.frame(x = location_source._geopoint_source_longitude, 
            y = location_source._geopoint_source_latitude, z = ReducedWaterLevel))

        xyzi <- interp(xyz$x, xyz$y, xyz$z, duplicate = "mean")
        image(xyzi, col = rev(brewer.pal(9, name = "YlGn")))
        contour(xyzi, add = TRUE)
        points(xyz, pch = 19)
        title(main = unique(df$month)[1])
    }
})
